Of the other ingredients Nasidienus boasts ofhav- ing invented two himself 3 one was the ‘eruca‚' which we call the rocket‚ a vege- table of the genus brassica, and the ‘inula campana‚' ‘ elccampane‚’ the ‘inula hele- nium' (ἑλένιον) of Linuaeus‚ a plant that grows in meadows and damp ground. It is used medicinally as a bitter. The last ingredient was the ‘ echinus,’ a prickly shell-fish, thrown in without being washed, for the benefit of its saline qualities: for which addition to the sauce he gives credit to one Curtillus.
